== Honey-Walnut Crostini ==

Place @honey{2%teaspoon} in a #cup{} of hot water to soften. Bring @cream cheese{4%tablespoon} to room temperature.

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees.

Slice @demi-baguette{1} crosswise into 8 rounds (16 rounds for 4 servings). Roughly chop @walnuts{½%ounce}.

Toss baguette slices on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Arrange in an even layer and toast on middle rack until golden brown, ~{4-6%minutes}. Remove from oven and let cool for ~{1%minute}.

Spread baguette slices with cream cheese. Top with walnuts, a drizzle of honey, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

> Serve crostini as an appetizer while you cook the rest of the meal.

== Mashed Potatoes and Green Beans ==

Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{16%ounce} into 1-inch pieces. (TIP: For smoother mashed potatoes, peel first.)

Place in a large #pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer. Cook until potatoes are tender, ~{10-15%minutes}, then drain.

Return potatoes to pot and keep covered (you'll finish them in Step 5).

While potatoes cook, trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Halve, peel, and mince half the @shallot{1}. Finely chop @chives{¼%ounce}.

Toss green beans on a second baking sheet with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

== Beef Tenderloin with Shallot Sauce ==

Meanwhile, pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season generously all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer beef to a #cutting board{} and tent with #foil{} to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for beef over medium-high heat. Add minced shallot and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @beef demi-glace{1}, @water{¼%cup}, and any resting juices from beef. Simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat. Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon}; taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

To pot with potatoes, add @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, @white cheddar cheese{½%cup}, a big pinch of salt, and pepper (if potatoes have cooled, return pot to low heat). Mash potatoes with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until smooth.

== To Serve ==

Slice beef against the grain.

Divide mashed potatoes, beef, and green beans between plates. Spoon pan sauce over beef. Sprinkle chives over potatoes. Serve.

== Chocolate Bundt Cakes ==

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together @crème fraîche{4%tablespoon}, @powdered sugar{2%ounce}, and @water{1%tsp} until smooth.

> The mixture may seem thick at first but will loosen up as you mix it.

Heat @chocolate bundt cake{2} according to package instructions.

Top cakes with crème fraîche icing and serve.